description.narrative: To ensure a COVID-19 responsive CP policy and legal framework,;UNICEF supported the formulation/adoption/localisation of key laws, policies and;plans, namely: adoption of the Anti-Child Marriage Act and ratification by Congress of the Anti-Rape Law increasing the age;from below 12 to below 16. Teleconsultations of Women and Child Protection Units were expanded in 3 regions to ensure access to essential CP services. Venues for children to participate were made possible due to the youth engagement strategy to address child online sexual abuse and exploitation. Innovations have been adopted such the digital delivery of multi-disciplinary curriculum for justice and social welfare professionals.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/12/2021
